[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/weak_2s"]
[Student "S"]
{One of the characteristics of Weak 2-Bids is that Responder often is unsure how high to go. That's why the 2NT bid is such a great tool. In this case you bid 2NT and partner says 3\D.  

You weren't sure whether to take partner to game or not. His 3\D bid tells you that he has a 9-11 point opener which includes the \DK. You couldn't hope for much more than that, so you bid 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "N:J2.KJ832.A7.KQJ3 AQ9874.65.986.T4 K.QT94.JT542.975 T653.A7.KQ3.A862"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1H 2S pass 3S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "830d418fa88eb06581d05b6afb771d4118a4faa3f4509cd75e91d8bb9dcfbf82"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/weak_2s"]
[Student "S"]
{You have a good Weak 2-Bid but North already opened. So you just make a Weak Jump Overcall of 2\S. South passes and partner raises to 3\S. North passes.  

Pass. Partner is in charge. If he had wanted you to bid again he could have forced you with 2NT.}

